(secondQuint)Study on Laparoscopic Spleen-Preserving No.

 10 Lymph Node Dissection for Advanced Middle or Upper Third Gastric Cancer.

 A prospective randomized comparison of laparoscopic spleen-preserving No.

 10 lymph node dissection for gastric cancer will be performed, to evaluate the short-term, long-term and oncological outcomes.

 The evaluation parameters are perioperative clinical efficacy, postoperative life quality, immune function and 3-year survival and recurrence rates.

